      • _GetType

        protected final java.lang.String _GetType()
        Description copied from class: VAudioPort
        Returns textual information of a concrete child's direct super type. To accomodate a special case where clients connect incompatible endpoints; We then throw an exception which reports the incompatibility with details about the conflicting types. If this application remains a Java application we could use Java introspection. However, it's going to be ported to C++, and there we'd have to resort to ominous tricks to get the name of the supertype of a class. It's much more straight forward to provide a short method that returns a string. It's just one of them things saying "ouch"...
        Specified by:
        _GetType in class VAudioPort
        Returns:
        Type information as text
